==English==

===Etymology===
{{PIE root|en|h₁ey}}
From {{etyl|LL.|en}} {{m|la|itinerarius||pertaining to a journey}}, neuter {{m|la|itinerārium||an account of a journey, a road-book}}, from {{m|la|iter||a way, journey}}; see {{m|en|itinerate}}, {{m|en|itinerant}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|en|/aɪˈtɪnəɹi/}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|en|/aɪˈtɪnəɹɛɹi/}}
* {{audio|en|en-us-itinerary.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|itineraries}}
# A written schedule of activities for a vacation or road trip.
# A [[route]] or proposed route of a [[journey]].
# An [[account]] or [[record]] of a journey.
# A [[guidebook]] for [[traveller]]s.

